{{Infobox organization | name = Chamber of Digital Commerce | genre = [[e-commerce]] | foundation = [[Washington, D.C.]], United States (July, 2014) | founder = Perianne Boring| area_served = United States industry | focus = Business advocacy | method = Political lobbying, [[Advocacy]], [[Public relations]] | website = {{URL|http://www.digitalchamber.org/}} }}
The '''Chamber of Digital Commerce''' is an [[United States|American]] [[advocacy group]] that promotes the emerging industry behind [[blockchain]] technology, [[bitcoin]], [[digital currency]] and [[digital asset]]s.<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.coindesk.com/chamber-of-digital-commerce/|title = Chamber of Digital Commerce Launches to Advance Bitcoin in Washington|author = Pete Rizzo|date = July 19, 2014|work = [[CoinDesk]]}}</ref><ref name="ibtimes-2014">{{cite web|url = http://www.ibtimes.co.uk/bitcoin-breakthrough-chamber-digital-commerce-opens-us-1457289|title = Bitcoin Breakthrough as Chamber of Digital Commerce Opens in US|author = Anthony Cuthbertson|date = July 21, 2014|work = [[International Business Times]] UK}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url = http://thehill.com/business-a-lobbying/225160-mellon-joins-bitcoin-advocacy-group|title = Mellon joins bitcoin advocacy group|author = Megan R. Wilson|date = November 24, 2014|work = [[The Hill (newspaper)|The Hill]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.ibtimes.co.uk/bitcoin-regulation-chamber-digital-commerce-talks-about-enlisting-former-jp-morgan-chief-blythe-1509174|title = Bitcoin regulation: Chamber of Digital Commerce talks about enlisting former JP Morgan chief Blythe Masters|author = Ian Allison|date = July 3, 2015|work = [[International Business Times]] UK}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Falcon Global Capital Hires Lobbyists to Promote Bitcoin in Washington|url=http://www.coindesk.com/falcon-global-capital-hires-lobbyists-to-promote-bitcoin-in-washington/}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Blockchain Technology Gets a Hearing Inside the Fed’s Headquarters|url=https://blogs.wsj.com/moneybeat/2016/06/07/blockchain-technology-gets-a-hearing-inside-the-feds-headquarters/}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.coindesk.com/chamber-digital-commerce-proposes-small-business-exemption-bitlicense/|title=Chamber of Digital Commerce Proposes Small Business Exemption for BitLicense|author=|date=|work=CoinDesk}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://cointelegraph.com/news/112442/chamber-of-digital-commerce-receives-donation-from-overstock|title=Chamber of Digital Commerce Receives Donation From Overstock|author=Ian DeMartino|date=4 September 2014|work=CoinTelegraph}}</ref>
==History== Headquartered in [[Washington, D.C.]], the organization was founded in July 2014 by [[Perianne Boring]]. In October 2014, the chamber received [[501(c) organization#501.28c.29.286.29|501(c)(6)]] non-profit status from the [[Internal Revenue Service]].<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1G1-389027976.html|title = Chamber of Digital Commerce Receives IRS Recognition|author = staff|date = October 16, 2014|work = Politics & Government Week via [[highbeam.com]]}}</ref> In 2015, economist and former [[JPMorgan Chase]] executive [[Blythe Masters]] was appointed to the advisory board.
In 2017, internet pioneer and [[Transmission Control Protocol]] (TCP) inventor [[Bob Kahn]] keynoted the DC Blockchain Summit at [[Georgetown University]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Dp4L92oI3Nk|title=Keynote: Robert E. Kahn}}</ref> Beginning in 2017, several [[multinational corporation]]s and international [[Bank holding company|financial services holding companies]] announced their intentions to join the Chamber of Digital Commerce including [[The Bank of New York Mellon|BNY Mellon]], [[BNP Paribas]], [[Accenture]], [[IHS Markit]], [[Cisco]], and [[Intuit]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://digitalchamber.org/bnp-paribas-bny-mellon-join-chamber-digital-commerce/}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20170427005017/en/IHS-Markit-Joins-Chamber-Digital-Commerce-World%E2%80%99s|title=IHS Markit Joins Chamber of Digital Commerce}}</ref> In October 2017, the Chamber of Digital Commerce, along with the U.S. Department of Commerce lead, the first Blockchain Certified Trade Mission to the United Arab Emirates.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.the-blockchain.com/2017/10/06/chamber-digital-commerce-u-s-department-commerce-lead-first-blockchain-certified-trade-mission-united-arab-emirates/|title=Chamber Of Digital Commerce And U.S. Department Of Commerce Lead The First Blockchain Certified Trade Mission To The United Arab Emirates|date=2017-10-06|work=Blockchain News|access-date=2017-10-09|language=en-US}}</ref>
== PAC (political action committee) == In August 2014, political news site ''[[The Hill (newspaper)|The Hill]]'' reported that the Chamber had registered a [[political action committee]] with the United States [[Federal Election Commission]]. As ''The Hill'' piece noted, “formation of the PAC is a sign of increasing maturity for Bitcoin and a signal that politicians could face political pressure to support virtual currencies.”<ref>{{cite news|title=Bitcoin lobby launches spending PAC|url=http://thehill.com/policy/technology/215862-bitcoin-lobby-launches-pac}}</ref> <ref name="hill-20140825">{{cite web|url = http://thehill.com/policy/technology/215862-bitcoin-lobby-launches-pac|title = Bitcoin lobby launches spending PAC|author = Julian Hattem|date = August 25, 2014|work = [[The Hill (newspaper)|The Hill]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url = http://thehill.com/policy/technology/216283-bitcoin-group-descends-on-congress|title = Bitcoin group descends on Congress|author = Julian Hattem|date = August 29, 2014|work = [[The Hill (newspaper)|The Hill]]}}</ref> <ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.jetlaw.org/2014/09/05/bitcoin-education-day-on-capitol-hill/|title = Bitcoin Education Day on Capitol Hill|author = Brenan Salgado|date = September 5, 2014|work = Vanderbilt Journal of Entertainment & Technology Law|publisher = [[Vanderbilt Law School]]}}</ref> <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.coindesk.com/chamber-digital-commerce-forming-bitcoin-political-action-committee/|title=Chamber of Digital Commerce to Form Fund for Pro-Bitcoin Politicians|author=|date=|work=CoinDesk}}</ref> <ref>{{cite web|url = http://dcinno.streetwise.co/2014/08/25/the-bitcoin-lobby-has-launched-their-very-own-pac-to-fight-regulation/|title = Politics News: The Bitcoin Lobby Has Launched Their Own PAC|author = Tess VandenDolder|date = August 24, 2014|work = DC Inno|publisher = [[Streetwise Media]]}}</ref> To date, however, the PAC has only raised $10,000 of which only $2,700 have been contributed to a candidate.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://docquery.fec.gov/cgi-bin/com_ind/C00567412/|title=FEC Disclosure Report Search Results|website=docquery.fec.gov|access-date=2017-01-25}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://docquery.fec.gov/cgi-bin/com_supopp/C00567412/|title=FEC Disclosure Report Search Results|website=docquery.fec.gov|access-date=2017-01-25}}</ref>
